comment:
I'm a deeply upset and concerned fan that one of my favorite idols and actor has been disgraced in the Hollywood industry due to the false accusations by one weak delusional little girl who screwed him over to climb up to fame and fortune. All of this happened because she didn't want to sign a prenuptial agreement and got angry at him because she can't get into his fortunes. Then she got all insecure, controlling, and jealous of him for it. Mind you. Resentment or the expression of resentment and distrust is a huge red flag in any relationship or marriage. If my partner/spouse express that they either resents me or distrust me in any way, well, then we need to leave each other alone and go our separate ways because that resenting and distrusting will be a constant pin poking up my arse.

Of course I'm with Team Johnny. I have many female friends who strongly agree that Amber Heard has taken advantage of this man as a woman and ruined all the hard work, support, awareness, and the credibility for real women out there who are actual victims of real domestic violence. Even they are not blind or deaf to all the evidence that exists out there that proves Amber Heard is the abuser and how much of Amber Heard's behavior is the same type of abuse found even in both men and women alike, it's a full blown trigger. This entire case should not be about favoritism of gender or a battle of the sexes here, it's about being held accountable for ones' actions and involvement. I side with the truth. Who's telling the truth? Definitely not Amber Heard.

Thus far, it appears that Johnny Depp has admitted to all of his actions in court in the honest way possible and he held himself accountable to try to clear his good name. As much as we would like for Amber Heard to be accountable for her actions (abuse) against Johnny Depp (sigh) . . . but we also know that's not going to happen because she likes to play games, like not answering yes and no questions and elaborating fake stories. It's not about age. It's about a person's personality and intentions. Age ain't nothing but a number, because if it were then my parents would not still be together all these years and they are 15 years apart. This is about "personality" , "compatibility", and "intentions". Amber Heard was NOT a good match for Johnny Depp. She seduced him for one thing and one thing only: HIS MONEY! Why else would she get so worked up and start fighting against him when he brought out the prenuptial agreement? And as far as her intentions goes, she is very CRUEL . . .therefore, I strongly disbelieve 100% of her accusations against Johnny Depp.  

#teamjohnny #supportjohnnydepp #justiceforjohnny
